names: TP53 is a tumor suppressor protein and responds to diverse cellular stresses to regulate expression of target genes, thereby inducing cell cycle arrest, apoptosis, senescence, DNA repair, or changes in metabolism. Mutations in this gene are associated with a variety of human cancers.

SP1 was the first characterized and still is one of the best studied mammalian transcription factors. It functions as a transcriptional activator of a variety of genes including house-keeping genes, cell cycle regulators and tissue-restricted genes.
